-- Brazil Stock Movers: Lojas Renner and Unicasa Were Active
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-04-27T21:01:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/brazil-stocks-br-malls-embraer-and-unicasa-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close. Preferred shares are
usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index fell 0.8 percent to 61,691.21.  Lojas Renner SA (LREN3 BS) rose 3.4 percent to 60.20 reais.
The retailer’s 25 percent fall in first quarter profit was due
to operating expenses such as store openings, “which is seen as
positive,” Leonardo Zanfelicio, an analyst at Concordia
Corretora, said by phone from Sao Paulo.  Unicasa Industria de Moveis SA  (UCAS3 BS) advanced 9.7
percent to 15.36 reais in debut trading today. The Brazilian
furniture maker and its shareholders raised as much as 425.6
million reais in an initial public offering on April 25. The
Bento Goncalves, Brazil-based company is selling as many as 30.4
million voting shares for 14 reais each, according to a
regulatory filing on April 26.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
